Create `src/scoring/scoreExisting.ts` exporting a single pure function:

```typescript
export function scoreExisting(inputs: ProjectInputs): ScoringResult
```

Implementation approach:
1. Score each criterion using helpers (scoreHighestTier, scoreCountCapped) and spec constants from EXISTING_SPEC
2. Build CriterionResult array with id, label, score, maxScore, mandatory/mandatoryMet for A1
3. Sum numeric scores (filter out any N/A — though existing engine should not produce N/A for its own criteria)
4. Apply pass logic: totalPoints >= 40 AND mandatoryMet (A1)
5. Return ScoringResult with passThreshold: 40

Do NOT include proposed-only criteria. The existing engine only returns criteria that exist in the existing test.

Reference EXISTING_SPEC from spec.ts for all numeric values — no magic numbers in the scoring function.
